# Imports And i18n

- Use `@/` for imports from `src`; `@` maps to `src` in Vite and TypeScript config.
- Use package names for dependencies, e.g. `react-i18next`; never import from `node_modules/...`.
- Avoid deep relative imports like `../../../../common/...`.
- Keep project imports stable: `@/common/...`, `@/modules/...`, `@/layouts/...`, `@/assets/...`.
- User-facing text must use `t('namespace.key')`.
- Supported locales are `az`, `en`, and `ru`; update all three locale files for new UI text.
- Persist selected language in `localStorage` key `lang`.
- Do not mix hardcoded Azerbaijani/English/Russian labels inside components.
